    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>The Herbig-Haro objects 1 and 2 are the archetype sources of their class and their study has produced several major advances in our understanding of star formation. Now it is known that a triple system resides within ~3" at the center of the region. One of the sources powers HH 1-2, the second one HH 501 and the third one HH 144. Since each source powers an outflow, each must also have a protoplanetary disk. We propose to use the unique potential of ALMA to image for the first time the three independent accretion disk structures and to search and image a circumbinary disk around the exciting sources of HH 1-2 and HH 501 and possibly a circummultiple disk around all three sources. This proposal will allow us to study a unique case exhibiting the formation of disks at different scales and around multiple scales.</prp:abstract>
